# .trivyignore — Accepted/acknowledged vulnerability suppressions
#
# All entries below are CVEs found in npm's own internal CLI packages
# (under /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/ in the Node.js base image).
# They are NOT part of the application code in /app/node_modules/.
#
# Risk justification:
#   - These packages (tar, glob, minimatch, cross-spawn) are used by the npm CLI
#     for package management operations (install, publish, extract).
#   - Our production containers run "node src/index.js" — npm is never invoked
#     at runtime, so these vulnerabilities have no exploitable attack surface
#     in the deployed application.
#   - We run "npm install -g npm@latest" in the Dockerfile to pull the newest
#     npm release; any remaining hits are un-patched upstream in the Node 20
#     base image's bundled npm version.
#   - Accepted risk: low. Remediation: upgrade base image to Node 22 when LTS.
#
# Owner: DevSecOps — review quarterly or on next Node LTS upgrade.

# cross-spawn in npm internals (ReDoS via malicious PATH argument)
# usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/cross-spawn
CVE-2024-21538

# glob in npm internals (command injection via malicious filenames)
# usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/glob
CVE-2025-64756

# minimatch in npm internals (ReDoS / catastrophic backtracking)
# usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/minimatch
CVE-2026-26996
CVE-2026-27903
CVE-2026-27904

# tar in npm internals (path traversal / arbitrary file write via malicious archive)
# usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/tar
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960
CVE-2026-29786
CVE-2026-31802

# ── Python base image build-tool CVEs (python:3.11-slim) ─────────────────────
#
# Risk justification:
#   - jaraco.context and wheel are Python packaging utilities bundled with pip
#     inside the python:3.11-slim base image.
#   - Our containers run "gunicorn app:app" — pip and its dependencies are
#     never invoked at runtime; no exploitable attack surface exists.
#   - Accepted risk: low. Remediation: upgrade to python:3.12-slim when stable.
#
# Owner: DevSecOps — review quarterly or on next Python base image upgrade.

# jaraco.context (pip/setuptools dep) — path traversal via malicious tar archive
CVE-2026-23949

# wheel (Python build tool) — privilege escalation via malicious wheel file
CVE-2026-24049
